HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 992
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend Yogi's Pizzeria & Ice
Cream Emporium.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should recognize those exemplary small businesses that,
through their unwavering commitment to excellence, are a credit to this State; and
WHEREAS, one such notable establishment is Yogi's Pizzeria & Ice Cream Emporium in
Nashville, one of the best neighborhood pizza places in Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, located at 4825 Trousdale Drive, Yogi's was opened in 2020 during the
COVID-19 pandemic; and
WHEREAS, for the past six years, the restaurant has been serving delicious stone-fired
Neapolitan-style pizzas with thin, charred crusts alongside mouthwatering calzones, wings, and
a selection of twelve flavors of ice cream from award-winning brands; and
WHEREAS, Yogi's has become a staple of its community; in addition to its welcoming
atmosphere, the restaurant has hosted events for the community, including cruise-ins that draw
a crowd and delight those who are interested in classic automobiles; and
WHEREAS, Yogi's is one of Nashville's most beloved pizza joints, and it is our privilege
to recognize this outstanding establishment; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we recognize the owners and employees of Yogi's Pizzeria & Ice Cream
Emporium, extending our congratulations for six successful years of operation and our best
wishes for many more to come.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
